    <h2>📐 Triangle Problem – What is <code>tan A</code>?</h2>

    <p><strong>Question:</strong></p>
    <p>Right triangle <strong>ABC</strong> is shown. What is the value of <code>tan A</code>?</p>

    <p><strong>Answer choices:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>A. <code>\(\frac{\sqrt{3}}{54}\)</code></li>
      <li>B. <code>\(\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}\)</code></li>
      <li class="answer">C. <code>\(\sqrt{3}\)</code></li>
      <li>D. <code>27\(\sqrt{3}\)</code></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>✅ Step-by-Step Solution</h2>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 1: Understand the triangle</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Triangle ABC is a right triangle with right angle at C.</li>
        <li>Angle B is 30°, so angle A must be 60° because angles in a triangle sum to 180°.</li>
        <li>The hypotenuse (side AB) is given as 54 units.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 2: Use 30°-60°-90° triangle ratios</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>In a 30°-60°-90° triangle, side ratios are:</li>
        <li>Opposite 30°: <code>x</code>, opposite 60°: <code>x√3</code>, hypotenuse: <code>2x</code></li>
        <li>So if hypotenuse AB = 54, then <code>2x = 54</code> → <code>x = 27</code></li>
        <li>This gives:
          <ul>
            <li>AC (opposite angle B or adjacent to A): <code>27</code></li>
            <li>BC (opposite angle A): <code>27√3</code></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 3: Apply the definition of tangent</strong>
      <ul>
        <li><code>tan(angle) = opposite / adjacent</code></li>
        <li>So <code>tan A = BC / AC = (27√3) / 27 = √3</code></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>✅ Final Answer:</strong> <span class="answer">Choice C. <code>√3</code></span>
    </div>
